Donald Trump, who has a public approval rating sitting below 40%, is due to address several issues including immigration and economic trade. NEW YORK - US President Donald Trump will give his first official State of the Union later on Tuesday. Trump, who has a public approval rating sitting below 40%, is due to address several issues including immigration and economic trade. Officials say the theme of President Trump’s speech would be “Building a Safe, Strong and Proud America”. Trump is expected to focus on five major policy areas, including jobs, the economy and national security. But whatever he says is likely to be overshadowed by signs the investigation into alleged Russia’s interference in the election is reaching a critical point. The mood in Washington DC is also said to be bitter following the recent government shutdown. A year into Trump’s Presidency, his approval rating is at a record low. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)